{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/handle-cancel-click-on-file-input/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Trishul Goel"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"5e217803-ebde-5ea8-8939-3dd2ec87835b","excerpt":"Ever Tried capturing cancel event on Browse file input type in HTML, tbh there is no direct way to do so :( But there is a workaround adding a bit of javascriptâ€¦","html":"<p>Ever Tried capturing cancel event on Browse file input type in HTML, tbh there is no direct way to do so :(</p>\n<p>But there is a workaround adding a bit of javascript. We can play with onfocus event of the BODY element.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/trishulgoel/static/49700d4f1b76ecdc0631b5cf964ee278/723cd/img1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.706422018348622%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"File input\"\n        title=\"Handle Cancel Click on File Input\"\n        src=\"/trishulgoel/static/49700d4f1b76ecdc0631b5cf964ee278/799d3/img1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/trishulgoel/static/49700d4f1b76ecdc0631b5cf964ee278/00d96/img1.png 148w,\n/trishulgoel/static/49700d4f1b76ecdc0631b5cf964ee278/0b23c/img1.png 295w,\n/trishulgoel/static/49700d4f1b76ecdc0631b5cf964ee278/799d3/img1.png 590w,\n/trishulgoel/static/49700d4f1b76ecdc0631b5cf964ee278/723cd/img1.png 872w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Example ->\nHTML</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;input type=&#39;file&#39; id=&#39;theFile&#39; onclick=&quot;initialize()&quot; /&gt;</code></p>\n<p>Javascript</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">var theFile = document.getElementById(&#39;theFile&#39;);\nfunction initialize()\n{\n    document.body.onfocus = checkIt;\n    console.log(&#39;initializing&#39;);\n}\n    \nfunction checkIt()\n{\n    if(theFile.value.length) \n      alert(&#39;Files Loaded&#39;);\n    else \n      alert(&#39;Cancel clicked&#39;);\n    document.body.onfocus = null;\n    console.log(&#39;checked&#39;);\n}\t\t</code></pre></div>\n<p>See it working <a href=\"https://tsl143.github.io/jsDemos/handleFileEvent/\">here</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Handle Cancel Click on File Input","date":"March 01, 2017","description":"handle-cancel-click-on-file-input"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/handle-cancel-click-on-file-input/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/enum-vs-tinyint/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"enum Vs tinyInt"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/get-list-of-global-npm-packages-installed/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Get list of all global npm packages installed"}}}}}